(31, '7 Days Congo Nile Trail Hiking', '958029.jpg', '351258.jpg', '452856.jpg', '940265.jpg', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>7 Days Congo Nile Trail Hiking is an exciting ten days hiking experience, which covers a wide range of fascinating attractions on Lake Kivu shores, with a distance of 227 km (141 miles) of beautiful landscapes, including rolling hills and clear water extends from Rubavu, continues through Rutsiro via the Karongi, Nyamasheke districts and ends at Rusizi District (Normally all hike is 12 days).\r\nBriefed itinerary:</p><br>\r\n<b>Day 1: Arrival</b><br>\r\n<p>Upon arrival, after completing customs and immigration formalities, you will be greeted by the driver guide, we transfer you to your hotel in Kigali or Rubavu; Once at the hotel, you will receive a detailed briefing on your trip.</p>\r\n<b>Day 2: Tour of Kigali or Rubavu</b><br>\r\n<p>After breakfast at the hotel; Kigali from your hotel, take a tour of Kigali, including the Kigali Genocide memorial Centre. Learn more about Rwanda’s history from pre-colonial times to the genocide of 1994. After visiting Kigali, the drive is to the west of the country Rubavu, a beautiful spot all by Lake Kivu. (On the way to Rubavu we will make stop- overs to see panoramic views of the country of a thousand hills. )</p><br>\r\n<b>Day 3: Gisenyi – Rwinyoni hiking</b><br>\r\n<p>After an early breakfast at your hotel and pre departure briefing by your guide and direct you to the trail start point for the beginning of an incredible 4 days of adventure, you will make your first trip overland to the village of Rwinyoni, northwest of Lake Kivu. From here you can enjoy the sun amazing on the lake shore. Reaches Kinunu we will make small walk to the village to discover the surroundings of this village. </p><br>\r\n<b>Day 4: Rwinyoni – Kinunu</b><br>\r\n<p>This morning, you can walk two hours to get to the famous village of fishermen Nkora. From this point, you can enjoy the view of the surroundings, fishermen returning from the tradition fishing in the night, children playing in the lake. The trail then leads to the tea plantations and banana, arrive at our accommodation at 1:00 pm. After lunch we will do a guided tour at the Kinunu washing station for your coffee experience. </p><br>\r\n<b>Day 5: Kinunu – Congo Nile via Musasa</b><br>\r\n<p>Today you will walk for 8 hours along Lake Kivu, interaction with the local community, enjoy the surrounding views and banana plantations, and visit the well-known Kinunu Catholic Church. Follow the trail of the coffee washing station in the village of Bwimana, Musasa, stopping to picnic by the lake. At 17:00, a 4 * 4 vehicle will join you to transfer you to a Night at Congo Nile Centre.</p><br>\r\n<b>Day 6: Congo Nile to Rubengera junction</b><br>\r\n<p>That day you will wake up early because you will have at least a minimum of 7 hours of walking to get to the junction Rubengera, following the track between fields of the community and climb the trail to the main road to Rubengera. At the junction asphalt Rubengera the best idea is to reach the city center of Kibuye. We go to Kibuye with Vehicle transportation. This day is the end of 4 days walking and hiking.</p><br> \r\n<b>Day 7: Kibuye – Kigali</b><br>\r\n<p>After Breakfast, go for a boat ride and visit different islands in the Kivu lake. After we visit the environmental museum in Kibuye before heading to Kigali for your departure flight or drop off at hotel.\r\nRecommendation: Hiking boots, rain gears,hat or cap and sunglasses.</p>\r\n', 'Active', '2024-02-28 20:36:11.064300'),
(32, '2 Days Rwanda Gorilla Trekking', '253215.webp', '183954.webp', '216115.jpg', '354114.jpg', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>2 days Rwanda Gorilla Trekking is an incredible short Rwanda safari package crafted to suit within your budget. This Rwanda short gorilla tour takes you to enjoy a close encounter with mountain gorillas in Volcanoes National Park in Ruhengeri, The Northern Province of Rwanda. Other than Gorilla Tracking, your gorilla tour also includes Kigali city expedition.&nbsp;</p><p>Your 2 days Rwanda Gorilla Trekking is a 2 day expedition, 1 night in Volcanoes N/Park, a home to some of the remaining 1063 of the world’s endangered mountain gorillas. Established in 1925, Rwanda’s Volcanoes National Park is a compact rain-forest protected area sitting in land area of only 160sq.kms. On your 2 days Rwanda Gorilla Trekking, your trip begins and ends in Kigali.</p><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\">Day 1: Travel up-to Volcanoes N/Park-Northern Province after City Tour</span></h4><h6 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\" class=\"\"><br></h6><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.8;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">Have the best of a leisurely cup of coffee/tea and after, vacate the lodge to begin a day with Kigali city tour. On your Kigali expedition, areas of interest include visiting the Kigali/Gisozi Genocide Site to have historical experience of the 1994 Rwandan Genocide; visit some of the best craft markets/shops in Kigali and other sites. About 2 hours shall be spent exploring Kigali city, one of the safest and cleanest cities in the world.</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.8;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">Have lunch in one of the best hotels or restaurants and after, vacate Kigali Capital City for Volcanoes National Park (VNP), about 2 to 3 hours’ drive. The park lies in Ruhengeri-The Northern Province of Rwanda. Arrive early to have adequate rest well-prepared for the next day’s main primate adventure-Gorilla Trekking. In the evening if time allows depending on your arrival, a cultural trip can be undertaken in the Iby’Iwacu Village then you return to retire for the night in the lodge.&nbsp;</span></p><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><br style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\">Where to stay</span></h4><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: Montserrat; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: initial; font-size: 22px;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><br style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"></span></h4><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.8;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">Basic/Budget: Kinigi Guesthouse or Muhabura Hotel</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.8;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">Mid-range/Moderate: Da Vinci Gorilla Lodge, La Palm Hotel/Le Bambou Gorilla Lodge</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.8;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">Luxury: Mountain Gorilla View Lodge, Virunga Lodge, Sabyinyo Silverback Lodge, Bisate Lodge</span></p><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><br style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\">Day 2: Gorilla Trekking &amp; return to Kigali Capital City-Rwanda&nbsp;</span></h4><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: Montserrat; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: initial; font-size: 22px;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><br style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"></span></h4><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.8;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">Join other visitors at Kinigi for briefing on Gorilla Tracking rules after you have enjoyed your hefty breakfast. By 7:00am, everyone is expected to be at Kinigi not only for briefing but also to be allocated to a gorilla group, park guide to lead you all through your gorilla trek. Only one of the 13 gorilla groups already habituated in Rwanda’s Volcanoes National Park shall be trekked by maximum of 8 visitors.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.8;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\"><br style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">Trekking with mountain gorillas in Volcanoes N/Park is unpredictable experience and usually, it takes 3-6 hours including the unmissable 1 hour of close encounter with mountain gorillas and photography. Return afterwards, meet your driver guide ready to get back to Kigali in the hotel/airport if the flight is scheduled in the evening.&nbsp;</span></p><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><br style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\">End of the 2 days Rwanda Gorilla Trekking</span></h4><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><br></span></h4><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Tahoma;\"><br></span></p>', 'Active', '2024-02-12 16:55:48.231827'),
(33, '3 Days Rwanda Gorilla Trekking', '801885.jpg', '949875.webp', '695813.jpg', '328435.webp', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>3 days Rwanda Gorilla Trekking offers you the best of Volcanoes National Park safari experience. On this short Rwanda safari, Gorilla Trekking is incredibly the main highlight. This will be a great opportunity for you to enjoy a magical encounter with the endangered mountain gorillas. Besides, this gorilla holiday includes Kigali city expedition, Golden monkey tracking and cultural experience in Iby’Iwacu Village. Your Rwanda Gorilla Trekking Tour in Volcanoes N/Park, starts and ends in Kigali.</p><h3 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><b>Brief itinerary&nbsp;</b></span></h3><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">Day 1:</span><span class=\"\" style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">Kigali city excursion &amp; drive to Volcanoes N.P Ruhengeri region</span></span></p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"border: 0px