r mid-range/moderate travelers</span></li><li style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); vertical-align: top; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; list-style-type: none; margin: 0px 1em; margin-inline: 2em 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.8;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">Mountain Gorilla View Lodge/Five Volcanoes Lodge-luxury/up market</span></li></ul><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><br style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"><b>Day 2: Gorilla Trekking Ruhengeri &amp; Community visit-Iby’Iwacu Village</b></span></h4><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: Montserrat; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: initial; font-size: 22px;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><br style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"></span></h4><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.8;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">Make adequate preparation early enough, have breakfast and after, carry some snacks plus bottled water. Head up to Kinigi to be briefed on Rwanda Gorilla Trekking guidelines by an expert from the park who also will allocate to you a gorilla family from 13 groups in Volcanoes National Park. When it clocks 8:00am, a knowledgeable guide leads you into the bamboo forest to spend about 2-6 hours searching for mountain gorillas. Once they have been located, you will be permitted 1 hour to be with these unique species.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.8;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">Walk back after photography and exploring in details about mountain gorillas behaviors. Have ample time to chill, share experiences and later in the evening, go for Iby’Iwacu Village walk/community tour. Return from your African cultural tour in Iby’Iwacu Village to relax and spend a night.</span></p><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: Montserrat; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: initial; font-size: 22px;\"><br></h4><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><b>Day 3: Golden monkey Tracking Ruhengeri &amp; depart</b></span></h4><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; font-family: Montserrat; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: initial; font-size: 22px;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><br style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"></span></h4><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 1.8;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\">After a morning tasty cup of tea/coffee, meet and greet your guide then connect to Kinigi to be briefed on Golden monkey Tracking guidelines. Today, your tour highlight is all about tracking to see golden monkeys in the wild and this will be 2-4 hours search including 1 hour of face to face encounter. Return to check out of the booked lodge and be transferred back to Kigali for departure flight.</span></p><h4 style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial; display: initial;\"><br style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: initial;\"><b>End of your 3 days Rwanda Gorilla Trekking &amp; Golden monkeys</b></span></h4><p style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-bottom: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; line-height: 2;\"><span class=\"\" style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\"><span style=\"border: 0px solid rgb(51, 51, 51); -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; display: initial;\"><br></span></span></p>', 'Active', '2024-02-12 17:01:58.525207'),
(34, '1 Day Akagera game drive', '865324.webp', '806816.webp', '608525.webp', '492838.webp', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>1 day Akagera Tour is one of the best short Rwanda safaris, taking you to explore and experience Akagera National Park. It is an exceptional Rwanda short game viewing tour trip crafted for you to indulge yourself into the magical African savannas of Akagera National Park. Your 1 day Akagera Tour takes you through a memorable big game trip-for you to see big mammal species including African savannah elephants, cape buffaloes, lions, leopards and rhinos.</p>\r\n<p>Akagera National Park is a beautiful savanna safari park, situated in the North-Eastern Rwanda and expands to border area with Tanzania. Akagera is a splendid big game safari park, featuring a mixture of savannah and a lush forest, papyrus swamps and rolling highlands. This is the only savanna park Rwanda has, hosting all the big five game in one habitat and taking a 1 day Rwanda Tour is amazingly such a great opportunity to uncover its hidden treasures.</p>\r\n<p>Akagera National Park Rwanda covers a vast area of about 1122sq.kms and protects diversity of wildlife in its distinct habitats. The varied species of wildlife to expect to keep an eye on while on 1 day Akagera Tour Rwanda moreover that the big 5 includes the Maasai Giraffes, Hippos, Zebras, Water bucks, Bushbucks, and over 500 bird species which range in different habitats especially savanna grassland, woodland, lakes, swamps and river Akagera.</p><br>\r\n<b>Day Trip to Akagera is a  Safari Game Drive & Lunch </b><br>\r\n\r\n<p>Wake up early from your hotel in Kigali, enjoy your delicious breakfast and later, meet your Rwanda tour leader for briefing. Have an insight into what your 1 day Akagera Tour is all about and then leave your hotel facility for 2 hours and 30 minutes’ drive trip to Akagera National Park (ANP) in North-eastern Rwanda.\r\nArrive early at Akagera National Park (ANP) Rwanda where you will begin your exploration that will last for 5-6 hours’ safari game drive. A safari game drive in Akagera National Park, entirely comes with amazing game sights and landscape views. A leisurely lunch be enjoyed in picnic place and it is best time to stretch body and hence after lunch game goes on as we exit for Kigali transfer. Other activities in the park are boat cruise, night safari, and birding.</p>\r\n<p>Recommended gears: green or khaki pant, long sleeve shirt, insect reparent, sneakers or any other comfortable shoes, sunglasses and expect long day driving.</p>\r\n', 'Active', '2024-02-27 19:17:02.801280'),
(35, '2 DAYS HIKING BISOKE VOLCANO', '936410.webp', '762379.jpg', '774858.jpg', '746650.jpg', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>Rwanda has 5 volcanoes within its boundaries, some it shares with Uganda and others with DR Congo with Sabyinyo volcano shared by all the three countries. The Volcanoes in Rwanda are all part of Volcano national park, they are Mt Muhabura, Mt Gahinga, Mt Sabyinyo, Mt Bisoke and Mt Karisimbi. Therefore when you hike to the peak of Sabyinyo, you have been to all the 3 countries at once.</p><p style=\"outline: none; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 28px; padding-top: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">Mount Bisoke Volcano hike to the Bisoke Crater lake is by far the most popular because of the beautiful scenery of the crater lake at the top. This is a day trip and hikers taking it on in 6 hours total whereas others take as long as 8 hours in today</span></p><p style=\"outline: none; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 28px; padding-top: 20px;\"><b style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.75rem;\">Day 1: Transfer from Kigali for the Mt Bisoke hiking Tour</b><br></p><p style=\"outline: none; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 28px; padding-top: 20px;\">Today your driver guide will pick you up from your hotel or airport and transfer to Musanze, near Volcanoes national park for your Mt Bisoke hiking tour. You will check in to your hotel in preparation for tomorrows activity.</p><h3 style=\"outline: none; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"outline: none; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\"><b>Day 2: Hike to Bisoke Crater Lake</b></span></h3><p style=\"outline: none; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 28px; padding-top: 20px;\">Your driver guide will transfer you for briefing at the park headquarter which starts at 7.00am. The trek starts early morning from the RDB offices in Kinigi. Your driver guide drops you at the office where you receive briefing and join other hikers to the Mt Bisoke. There are different groups of people at the headquarters going for different activities in Volcanoes national park which include, gorilla trekking, golden monkey trekking and hiking different volcanoes.</p><p style=\"outline: none; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 28px; padding-top: 20px;\">Your hiking guide will brief you on expectations while you hike Mt Bisoke and what you should be aware of. After the briefing, your driver guide will transfer you to the starting point which is about 30 minutes away because of the nature of the nature of the road. After you have experienced your Bisoke hiking, you will be transferred back to Kigali for drop off at the hotel or airport.</p>', 'Active', '2024-02-18 17:53:02.696520'),
(36, '1 Day Golden monkeys and Ibyiwacu Cultural Village', '963170.jpg', '617387.webp', '10798.jpg', '177905.webp', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>Early morning is driving to the park headquarters for a briefing of trekking Golden monkeys and at around 11hoo normally the activity is done and then proceed with the Iby’iwacu Cultural Village which  is nestled in the\r\nhills of Musanze, quite near Kinigi and the Mountain Gorillas. It is an easy side trip for anyone visiting the Gorillas or Golden Monkeys of Volcanoes National Park, but especially convenient for those staying in Musanze.</p>\r\n<p> Ibyiwacu cultural village gives visitors a chance to share with local people on home and heritage treasures including lifestyles, activities, artifacts and ways of living of Rwandans back in time. Ibyiwacu Cultural Village showcases the ways of living, traditional lifestyles and dances. Ibyiwacu Cultural Village gives you a rare chance to meet local people, in their environment, with a taste of our culture and traditions. Be genuinely welcomed by the community as a special visitor while they proudly present to you aspects of their traditions and beliefs. The only way to get to know people, is getting close and interacting with local people, and taking part in their daily activities and most of all with them.</p>\r\n<b>Recommended gears: Hiking boots, gaiters, hut or cap, rain jacket</b>\r\n\r\n', 'Active', '2024-02-27 19:12:17.409956');
