(39, '3 Days Rwanda and Uganda Gorilla Trekking Tour Uga', '24537.jpg', '360546.webp', '577860.jpg', '977243.jpg', 'Uganda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>3 Days Rwanda and Uganda Gorilla Trekking Tour is the best and Short Uganda and Rwanda Safaris Tour package designed for you to get up close with a group of mountain gorillas while in their natural habitat in both countries. Bwindi Impenetrable National Park is in southwestern Uganda, 530 kilometers that is approximately 8-10 hours’ drive from Entebbe or Kampala city center and 3-4 hours by road from Kigali.</p>\r\n<p>It covers an area of 331sq.kms and its establishment in 1991 was mainly to offer refuge to mountain gorillas that today remain fewer than 1004 on earth. Bwindi Impenetrable National Park is home to half the total number of mountain gorillas that currently thrive in the world.</p><p>Gorilla trekking safaris in Uganda and Rwanda are conducted in Bwindi National Park and Mgahinga National Park(Uganda) and Volcanoes National Park in Rwanda. In Bwindi Impenetrable National Park, gorilla trekking adventures are done in only the Ruhija, Nkuringo, Rushaga, and Buhoma region, each with habituated gorilla families. Note, only 8 visitors are allowed to trek one habituated family per day and you are accompanied by an ranger guide.</p><p>The 3 Days Bwindi Gorilla Trekking Tour starts from Uganda or Rwanda with pick up by one of our professional driver guides or do the same tour starting from Kigali International Airport/Hotel in Kigali via Katuna or Chanika border posts with opportunity to visit the scenic Lake Bunyonyi and Lake Mutanda for you to embark on community walk or canoe ride while enjoying the breathtaking views of rolling hills or scenic islands.</p> <p>Alternatively, take a flight from Entebbe International Airport or Kajjansi airfield, Kihihi or Kisoro airstrip then connect to Bwindi National Park.</p>What to expect on 3 Days Bwindi Gorilla Trekking Tour</span></h4><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; padding-inline-start: 48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: none; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 23pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap: wrap;\">Gorilla trekking in Bwindi Forest national park 0r Mgahinga National park(Uganda) and Volcanoes National park (Rwanda)</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: none; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 23pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap: wrap;\">One hour of magical encounter with mountain gorillas</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: none; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 23pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap: wrap;\">Stopover at Equator when trip has started from Kampala.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: none; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 23pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap: wrap;\">Breathtaking views of the landscape in southwestern Uganda among others</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: none; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 23pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-wrap: wrap;\">Photo taking</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: none; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: 23pt;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 15pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><br></p></li></ul><h5 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 23pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding: 0pt 0pt 15pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Brief itinerary of our 3 Days Gorilla Trekking Safari Bwindi Uganda</span></h5><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding: 0pt 0pt 15pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Day 1: Transfer from Entebbe, Kampala or Kigali to Bwindi Impenetrable National Park&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding: 0pt 0pt 15pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Day 2: Gorilla trekking in Bwindi National Park and transfer to Volcanoes National park or vice versa</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 15pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Day 3: Return to Entebbe, Kampala or Kigali</span></p><div><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(102, 102, 102); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\"><br></span></div></span>', 'Active', '2024-02-28 20:39:10.022742'),
(40, '15 Days Best of Uganda and Rwanda Safari with prim', '835880.jpg', '358409.png', '823080.jpeg', '993409.webp', 'Uganda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<b>DAY1: Kigali City tour excursion and Akagera NP transfer</b>\r\n<p>1st day is Country of thousand hills exploration and starts with pick up,kigali city excursion experience with Kigali Genocide Memorial and then, transfer in a wildlife safari in Akagera National Park, The park was named after the river Akagera flowing up to the lake Victoria considered as source of Nile,  a big five park with 10 lakes full of hippos and Nile crocodiles. </p><br>\r\n<b>DAY 2: game drive  akagera and Night safari</b>\r\n \r\n<p>After breakfast in accommodation within Akagera National park, it is then game drive that ends back to the hotel and wait for night safari to start 18hoo where you check for nocturnal animals, around 21 hoo , visitors are back to the lodge for overnight stay and dinner.</p><br>  \r\n<b>DAY 3: full game drive and boat experience.</b><br>\r\n<p>After morning breakfast, it is pick up at your lodge, Full game drive in Akagera national park, with chance of spotting big 5 of animals (lion, leopard,rhino, elephant and buffalo)as well as different species of antilope, giraffe, zebra, poumba, hippos, crocodile etc..\r\nAnd at 16:30h is to be ready at boat launch point for boat ride experience which is mostly checking for aquatic animals and birds mostly water ones as other aquatic animals as well as  others that should come to quench thirsty.</p>\r\n  \r\n<b>Day 4: transfer to the border</b>\r\n<p>After breakfast, Check out in the morning with packed lunch, head to the border with Uganda, after boarder process, it is a transfer at the booked accomodation for relaxation and overnight stay for next day adventures.</p><br>\r\n \r\n<b>Day 5: Gorilla tracking in Bwindi impenetrable forest or Mgahinga NP </b><br>\r\n<p>Wake up early in the morning, have breakfast and proceed to the park offices with your picnic packed lunch and water. Have a briefing from the park rangers about the gorillas, and the adventure starts by 8am you will be allocated to the gorilla family together with your ranger guides on duty. The trekking can take anything from 2-8 hours. Once you arrive at the gorillas, you are allowed to spend one full hour with them as you stand in a distance of 7 meters away learning, and observing their characters. After Gorilla trekking drive back to the lodge for relaxation. And later in the evening go for Batwa/pygmies experience and back to the lodge for an overnight</p><br>\r\n \r\n<b>Day 6: Transfer to queen Elizabeth National Park</b><br>\r\n<p>After morning breakfast, the continuation is  to Queen Elizabeth for a 2hours afternoon boat cruise along kazinga channel that connects Lake Edward and George. Boat cruise safari on this channel is one of the highly recommended adventurous activities to visitors of Queen Elizabeth national park. The cruise will bring you very close to several mammals like Hippos, Nile crocodiles and buffalos, elephants and many others plus water birds. Later drive to the lodge to spend the evening relaxing. Dinner and overnight.</p>\r\n\r\n<b>Day 7: Queen Elizabeth morning game drive and Transfer to Kibale National park</b>\r\n<p>Today after breakfast, drive to Kasenyi plains found in north eastern part of the park. For the  morning game drive searching for wildlife species. Queen Elizabeth is understandably one of  the Uganda’s popular parks and an ideal habitat for classic big game such as the four mammals  of the big five family of the African savannah. This park is known for its variety wildlife species  with over 95 mammal species which includes four big mammals, big cats and other predators, 10 species of primates, aquatic mammals and about 600 recorded bird species. After the morning game drive, we will embark on the road to Kibale national park. One of the best scenic  drives in Uganda. Arrive early evening with relaxation as for preparation for the next big day.</p><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Day 8: Chimpanzee Trekking</b></br>\r\n<p>After morning breakfast the drive is towards Kibale forest national park, which is the top safari destination in Africa for chimpanzee trekking with your picnic packed lunch and enough water. Meet your ranger guide at the park office and then enter the rainforest to begin the search for the man’s closest beings, this will take about 2-5 hours to find the chimpanzees. Upon seeing them, you will spend 1 full hour with the chimpanzees while taking pictures and observing their characters. Drive back to the lodge in the afternoon, refresh and embark a 2- 3 hours nature walk at bigodi swamp and community walk. Then drive back to your lodge for Dinner and overnight stay.</p>\r\n\r\n \r\n<b>Day 9: Transfer to Murchison Falls National Park and visit top of the falls</b>\r\n<p>After an early morning breakfast, the continuation with safari is to Murchison falls located in the North western Uganda. The source of happiness for nature lovers, reaching in the late afternoon where the welcome is by hundreds of baboon lined along the road. On arrival, visit Murchison falls to enjoy the breathtaking views and great sound of the falls as it  squeezes itself through the narrow gorge of only 7metres wide, then drops 43metres into a pool that creates a strong thunderous sound that is so lovely. The tour to the top of the falls takes about an hour starting from the view point to the bottom. After proceed with the drive to the northern sector of the park cross the river Nile to check in at the booked lodge.</p>\r\n \r\n<b>Day 10: Morning Game drive at Murchison National Park and afternoon Boat cruise</b>\r\n \r\n<p>Wake up early to have a cup of coffee, get your packed breakfast and head out to the northern  sector where superb game drive safaris are carried out. During the game drive, the professional driver guide help visitors  to spot several animals and share with them a lot of informations regarding various wildlife species  such as caped buffalo, elephants, Ugandan kobs, Jackson hartebeest, Rothschild giraffes and  many other animals. Have a short break to enjoy your breakfast and after proceed with the game drive. Later in the afternoon leave the park to lodge for lunch. After lunch drive to the Victoria Nile for the boat cruise. The boat cruise goes upstream from the calm Victoria Nile to  the base of Murchison falls, stopping a few metres from the devils cauldron of the falls which gives an amazing view of the falls and see how the river Nile drops into pool. There after the game, drive to the lodge for an overnight.</p>\r\n<b>Day 11: Transfer to Kampala via Ziwa Rhino Sanctuary</b><br>\r\n<p>Wake up in the morning drive towards Kampala the capital city of Uganda, On the way, guests visit Ziwa rhino sanctuary, located in Nakasongola district, the home of Uganda’s rhinos, where visitors get chance to see white rhinos in their natural environment, up close to their feet, which provides unforgettable experience. The rhino sanctuary is the only place in Uganda where you can see white rhinos in the wild, after the experience, then is  lunch. Thereafter drive to the booked lodge for an overnight (or night life experience if interested). </p> \r\n \r\n<b>Day 12: Game drive at Mburo National Park</b><br>\r\n \r\n<p>On this day, after morning breakfast, visitors get on the road for Lake Mburo where have a stopover at Uganda equator line which is believed to separate the planet into two parts: the Northern and Southern hemisphere. While here visitors take some memorial photos with one foot in the southern hemisphere and another one in the Northern hemisphere after have lunch, visit some craft shops to buy some souvenirs which are fully designed in a Ugandan local art. Thereafter proceed to Lake Mburo National Park for an evening game drive or relaxation.</p>\r\n \r\n<b>Day 13: Morning Walking Safari in Mburo</b><br>\r\n \r\n<p>After early morning breakfast, go for walking safari closed to the Giraffes and other animals like Zebras, Warthog and many others or go for Jungle horseback riding safari in the park.  In the afternoon is transferback to the capital city of uganda for overnight stay.</b><br>\r\n<b>Day 14: Kampala City Tour</b><br>\r\n<p>Morning after breakfast, visitors embark in the vehicle to explore different parts of the main city of Uganda like Kabaka’s(King) palace, Makelele University, Uganda Museum, Bahai temple, Monkey forest, waterfall, local market and experience boda-boda riding. After then, go back to the Hotel for relaxation and overnight stay.</p><br>\r\n<b>Day 15: Transfer and occasional activities along the way</b>\r\n<p>On this last day of the safari, the activities to do are specified according to the transfer road but this maily includes cultural and heritage activities.</p> \r\n \r\n<b>This includes:</b>\r\n- Gorilla permit(s)<br>\r\n- Chimpanzee permit(s)<br>\r\n-Nature walk fee and community walk<br>\r\n-Park entrances.<br>\r\n- Boat cruises.<br>\r\n-walking safari<br>\r\n- Transportation on 4x4 transport with gas and a driver/guide.<br>\r\n-  Accommodation on a full board (Dinner, Breakfast and packed lunch)<br>\r\n-  Drinking water.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>EXCLUSIONS</b>\r\n-Activities not mentioned in the Itinerary<br>\r\n-Phone calls and bar bills.<br>\r\n-Items of personnel nature, entertainment and any other optimal activity.\r\n From 5495 USD/pax<br>\r\n Recommendation: rain gears, hiking boots, insect reperent, hat, rayban glasses.<br>\r\n', 'Active', '2024-02-28 21:04:56.993355');

