INSERT INTO `tours` (`id`, `tour_name`, `img1`, `img2`, `img3`, `img4`, `country`, `province`, `district`, `details`, `status`, `added_time`) VALUES
(34, 'Nyungwe National Park', '327326.jpg', '803633.jpg', '562219.jpg', '53307.jpg', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>Nyungwe  National Park is one of the four national parks in Rwanda and among the top destinations in the country. This is not only the place for relaxation but also one of the places for adventure and insight into Rwanda‘s single beauty. This forest is one of the oldest rainforests in Africa and it is UNESCO World heritage site.</p>\r\n<p>This protected and among oldest rainforests in Africa covers between 1020 sq meters and is a five hour of driving from Kigali capital city of the country , this long drive to Nyungwe also gives the guests an opportunity to observe the country’s diverse sceneries and the imposing landscape as you move to the main attraction. Once you get to the park, you will then prepare to join the most unbelievable adventures you may ever had such as the canopy walk, Hikings, waterfalls, chimpanzees trekking, black and white colobus monkeys etc.</p>\r\n<p>In addition, the beautiful scenery large, centuries-old trees and the added thick forest, and this extraordinary tropical forest is a shelterer 13 species of primates, over 1000 plant species, and more than 300 bird species including famous Turaco(Great blue, Ross’s, and Rwenzori ).  The bridge is  160m long and 70 m hight suspension canopy walkway that will give you the excitement that can hardly be compared to anything else.</p>\r\n<p>Getting to the canopy is also about 2 hours from the starting point at Uwinka visitor Centre and can be done one hectic day from kigali . The forest is on a mountain and the hike is also slippery due to the mere fact that the ground on which the guests’ trek is moist, wet and muddy when rained. This bridge adjourned between the huge trees one on the feel of the fresh air and incomparable view . Apart from the freshness in the air and the wonderful aerial view of the trees, you will also enjoy the sights of the fantastic birds that fly across as you enjoy the walk. It was opened in 2010 and it’s the only one of its kind in East Africa and the third on the African continent. This bridge canopy walkway also gives a unique face to face meetings with the butterflies, different plant species, birds and the monkeys.</p>\r\n<p>The hardwood trees also occupy the upper canopy as the lower part is dominated by the large selection of the purple orchids and the lush flora as well as fauna that curl better in the higher altitudes.</p>\r\n<p>And apart from the canopy walk, this national park also offers many trails into the different parts of the forest for the hikers and the walkers. All the guided walks start from the central Uwinka reception Centre, the western Gisakura, Gisovu  entrances as well as the eastern Kitabi entrance.</p>\r\n<p>Since the view might be good from above, this attraction is also good from the forest floor. There is also a network of the ten mud trails that takes you deep into the heart of the forest.</p>\r\n<p>And finally, you will reward yourself after the 10km hike with a visit to Nyungwe’s Ishuno waterfalls that are beautiful. It may also be small in size, but this calm waterfall strikes its way and the breeze to which one is also welcomed will feel one of life’s greatest pleasures.\r\nThis walkway of about 200m also hangs across a steep and deep valley that is filled with thick forest. This walk gives breathtaking views across the misty forest and the sightings at the eye level of the variety of wildlife that lives in the canopy.</p>\r\n<p>This canopy walk also takes close to 2 hours and its starting and endpoint being Nyungwe National park reception - the Uwinka tourist reception center. The first 200m is a walk along the forest trail under the thick canopies for an opportunity of viewing the ground level nature before taking on the canopy walkway to get to the top level of the forest. The prominent sightings here include; the monkeys, including the blue monkeys, L’Hoest monkeys, black and white colobus, the red-tailed monkeys and the birds. The minimum age for this walk is 6 years and the kids must be escorted by the adults. More so, the activity is present throughout the whole year. The chances of rain failing are high so, remember to carry a raingears, hiking boots, insect reperent, cameras to make your experience memorable, water, and hut or cap. The walking sticks are provided free of charge. About the difficulty, this hike is so easy and takes only 2 hours to complete it.</p>\r\n<p>Chimpanzees tracking, also takes place in this park, and it is early morning activity so it is better to stay over night around the park or inside accommodation  before the experience day. So after driving 30 min to 2 hours to the starting point depending of the location of your accommodation, visitors get briefing from park ranger and start, the activity can last for 3 hour to all 6 hours depending of the movement of these apes and then visitors spend one hours with them. The same necessaries are recommended as for canopy walk experience(rain gears, hiking boots, camera, insect repellent, hut or cap, and drinking water)</p>\r\n<p>Hikings are differents accordingly, there steep, long, easy, medium and strong so depends to someone abilities and capabilities to choose so among these hikings includes the waterfall experience such as Kamiranzovu, Ndambarare,Isumo etc. This is not recommended to somebody with health complications such as heart shortness, lungs.</p>\r\n<p>So beyond the above experiences, we can also do activities such as tea plantation experience, nature walk, traditional dancing, biking, bee keeping experiences etc.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Active', '2024-02-27 18:15:46.135722'),
(35, 'Volcanoes National park', '253215.webp', '801885.jpg', '253215.webp', '253215.webp', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>Volcanoes National Park is located in North-Western part of Rwanda, a home of endangered Mountain Gorillas and threatened Golden Mankeys in the foothills of 5 dormant volcanoes, so visiting this site is in the unique opportunities to see gorillas in their natural habitat which is unforgettable, a life experience and some even say life changing.</p>\r\n<p>Encounters with gorillas as they go about their daily lives, are carefully managed, with expert trackers and guides leading small groups of tourists up bamboo-covered slopes to spend a precious and awe-inspiring hour just a few feet away from the gentle creatures, tracking gorillas is done early morning as around 07hoo, and it is done first by briefing of the parks’ ranger and driving to the starting point of trekking, from Kigali International Airport to this site is 2.5 hours of driving and trekking this gentle great apes can take 3 to 6 hours according to their movement.</p>\r\n<p>Among other activities in this park, there are Golden Monkeys tracking, Bisoke hiking, Karisimbi hiking, Sabyinyo hiking, Muhabura hiking ,Gahinga Hiking, Buhanga Eco Park, and exploring Musanze Caves. Once in this place, don’t miss out the cultural experience (Gorilla guardians’ or Iby’Iwacu experience)</p>', 'Active', '2024-02-28 21:15:52.015308'),
(36, 'Gorilla Tracking', '601237.jpg', '913376.jpg', '699742.jpg', '191886.webp', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', 'The unique opportunity to see gorillas in their natural habitat is unforgettable, some even say life changing. Encounters with gorillas as they go about their daily lives are carefully managed, with expert trackers and guides leading small groups of tourists up bamboo-covered slopes to spend a precious and awe-inspiring hour just a few feet away from the gentle creatures.', 'Active', '2023-08-11 13:45:34.969650'),
(38, 'Queen Elizabeth National Park', '52740.jpg', '797980.jpg', '327456.jpg', '195073.jpg', 'Uganda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>Queen Elizabeth National Park is Uganda’s most popular savanna reserve and has the widest variety of wildlife of any Ugandan park. </p> <p>The variety of habitats include grassland savanna, forests, wetlands and lakes. This provides the setting for an extensive range of large mammals and primates. Four of the Big five are present and regularly seen. Rhinos are absent.</p>', 'Active', '2024-02-27 18:31:24.390720'),
(39, 'Bwindi Impenetrable National Park', '608850.jpg', '462304.jpeg', '360634.jpg', '900998.jpg', 'Uganda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>The name Bwindi is derived from Runyakitara word ‘Mubwindi’ which means ‘’a place full of darkness’’. Bwindi Impenetrable National Forest is located in south western part of Uganda and is home of many families of mountain gorillas and hence the best place in Uganda to track mountain gorillas.</p><p>The forest is also a bird-watcher’s paradise with 350 species recorded, including many Albertine Rift endemics, the park is 330 square kilometers and altitude averaging 1160-2607 m above sea level, on the edge of the Albertine Rift and western branch of East African Rift and hence, Bwindi Impenetrable National park is UNESCO World Heritage Site and it is the most biologically diverse place on Earth, it is near the border with Democratic Republic of Congo and 25 km to north of virunga mountains. So Mountain Gorillas tracking is the most activity as birdwatching and cultural experiences can be done. </p>', 'Active', '2024-02-27 18:28:38.292965'),
(40, 'Kidepo Valley National Park', '338072.jpeg', '265407.jpg', '68747.webp', '532693.jpg', 'Uganda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>The Kidepo Valley is in a remote corner of the country which is rarely visited by tourists, due to the expense and difficulty in getting there. The park is a true wilderness destination for the adventurous and has excellent wildlife-viewing during the Dry season, featuring several species not encountered anywhere else in the country.</p><p class=\"has-black-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-edfdae629845fa212c6c5ffa06e59007\" style=\"\"><b>Size: </b>1,442km² / 557mi²</p><p class=\"has-black-color has-text-color has-link-color wp-elements-827f5fda2cfa0d3e75524ecf266737db\" style=\"\"><b>Altitude:</b> 999-2,720m / 3,278-8,924ft</p>', 'Active', '2024-02-18 18:00:03.495384'),
(41, 'Akagera National Park', '666565.jpg', '950648.jpg', '865937.webp', '649507.jpg', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>Akagera National Park is located in the North East of Rwanda along the border with Tanzania. Although, founded in 1934, much of the park was re-allocated as farms and in 1997 the park was reduced in size from more than 2,700 sq km (nearly 10% of the surface area of Rwanda) to its current extent of 1,122 sq km. Since 2010, a joint venture with African Parks has seen Akagera return to its former glories.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>It is named after the Akagera River that flows along its eastern boundary and feeds into a labyrinth of 10 lakes of which the largest is Lake Ihema and the first from bottom up(south to North). The forest fringed lakes, papyrus swamps, savannah plains and rolling highlands combine to make Akagera amongst the most scenic of reserves anywhere in Africa. It has exceptional levels of biodiversity and forms the largest protected wetland in central Africa.</p>\r\n<p>Akagera combines well with Nyungwe and the Volcanoes NP to offer a great safari element as it is home to many large plains game species as well as species restricted to the papyrus swamps such as the Sitatunga and the sought-after Shoebill Stork. Notable plains game include lions, savannah elephants, buffaloes, rhinoceros, zebra, waterbuck, roan, impala, eland, waterbuck and topi antelopes among others such as warthog, maasai giraffe etc. Of the primates, olive baboons, vervets and blue monkey can be seen during the day, with bushbabies, serval cats, spotted hyena, leopard that often can be seen in night drives.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Lions were re-introduced in 2015 after last seen of this carnivores in 2005 and assumed to be extincted in this reserve as the introduction of black and white rhinoceros since 2017 . This has restored Akagera as a home of  ‘Big 5’ status.\r\nDue to its wide variety of habitats, Akagera is an important ornithological site with nearly 500 bird species. The rare and elusive shoebill stork shares the papyrus with other rarities such as the exquisite papyrus gonolek and countless other water birds that inhabit the wetlands in large numbers, so activities in this park are day game drive, night game drive,boat ride experience and birdwatching.</p>\r\n', 'Active', '2024-02-27 18:26:17.632130'),
(42, 'Cultural Experiences', '353755.jpg', '707667.jpg', '86803.jpg', '152396.jpg', 'Tanzania', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>Centuries of music, dance, history and hospitality are waiting for you in Rwanda, While it might have been the gorillas that entice you to Rwanda, it is the people of Rwanda who will keep you coming back.</p>\r\n<p>Ancient traditions of honors and hospitality run strong here, and anybody who takes the time to discover Rwandan culture for themselves will find a proud and unique people, happy to welcome you into their lives and introduce you to their traditions.</p>\r\n<p>Music and dance play an indispensable role in everyday life here, and performances range from dashing demonstrations of bravery and prowess to humorous songs, light-hearted dances, and rural artistry with roots in traditional agriculture. Traditional songs are often accompanied by a solitary lulunga — a harp-like instrument with eight strings—while more celebratory dances are backed by a drum orchestra, which typically comprises seven to nine members who collectively produce a hypnotic and exciting explosion set of intertwining rhythms. Below we list different cultural experiences that you can easily incorporate into your trip to Rwanda.\r\nKigali Museums (Campain Against Genocide Museum, Kandt House Museum, and Rwanda Art Museum)</p><br>\r\n<b>King Palace Museum</b><br>\r\n<b>Ethnographic Museum</b><br>\r\n<b>Environmental Museum </b><br>\r\n<b>National Liberation Museum</b><br>\r\n<p>Iby’Iwacu or Gorilla Guardians Experience\r\nRecommended gears: sneakers or any other comfortable shoes, sunglasses, hat or cap and expect mixed driving.</p>\r\n', 'Pending', '2024-02-28 21:12:05.390899'),
(43, 'Gishwati Mukura National Park', '434043.jpg', '377914.jpg', '816764.jpg', '435294.jpg', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>The recently established in Rwanda, this biosphere reserve is a home of chimpanzees , Golden Monkeys and different species of birds so activities are such as chimpanzees tracking, golden monkey tracking, birdwatching, nature walk and hiking as well as exploring kivu lake and Pfunda tea plantation experience.</p>', 'Active', '2024-02-27 18:44:01.035809'),
(44, 'Murchison Falls National Park', '151428.jpg', '678853.jpg', '354992.jpg', '294991.jpg', 'Uganda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>Murchison Falls National Park is located in Noth Western part of Uganda,spreading inland from the shores of lake Albert and around the Victoria Nile, the explorers John Speke and James Grant were the first to explore and visit this conservation area. It is the largest park in Uganda with over 3800 skm, specialised in game drives, a home of Leopard,Giraffes, Elephants and hartebeest&nbsp; and then enjoying boat to the base of falls seeinge.</p><p> nile crocodile and hippos is so fascinating. The park is also a home of more than 450 recorded species of birds including grey parrot, dwarf kingfisher, goliath heron and many more</p>', 'Active', '2024-02-27 18:47:28.945219'),
(45, 'Kibale National park', '527168.jpg', '893632.jpg', '883629.jpg', '72210.png', 'Uganda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>Kibale National Park is located in Western part of Uganda with 776 square kilometers and range between 1100 and 1600 m above sea level, established in 1993, home of 13 primates species including unforgettable experience of chimpanzees tracking,galagos, red tailed monkey, mountain monkey,olive baboon,black and white colobus as well as red colobus monkeys which make it the highest diversity and concentration of the primates in Africa.</p><p> The park isn’t only with primate but also a population of elephants that travel between Queen Elizabeth National Park and Kibale National Park. Among others, the park is a home of sitatunga,duikers,bushbucks, giant forest hog, common warthog and african buffaloes as well as otters.', 'Active', '2024-02-27 18:51:47.709944'),
(46, 'Ziwa Rhino Sanctuary', '602705.jpg', '571292.jpg', '127078.jpg', '593267.jpg', 'Uganda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>It is located in North of Kampala capital city of Uganda long Kampala-Gulu highway, covers 70 square kilometers, established 2005, only place in uganda to observe these endangered creatures in wild, the only place in the country to see rhinos on foot.</p><p> So, this is a best experience with trained rangers to take visitors around and make it last forever with good pictures near rhinos but also in a safe distance.</p>', 'Active', '2024-02-27 18:55:22.135822'),
(47, 'Mgahinga National Park', '208908.jpg', '463916.jpg', '434483.jpg', '995136.jpg', 'Uganda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>A place where Gold meets Silver, this is due that the place is a home of Mountain Gorillas and Golden monkeys, found in 1991, after evacuating indigenous people for the purpose of conservation of these endangered creatures, covering 34 square kilometers which makes it the smallest park in The Pearl of Africa and located in south western part of Uganda near the border with Rwanda and DRC, Mgahinga is located is South Western.</p><p> Activities in the park are trekking gorillas, Tracking Golden monkeys, Birdwatching, Hiking, nature walk as well as cultural and community experiences. </p>', 'Active', '2024-02-27 18:59:05.174892'),
(48, 'Kidepo Valley National Park', '37582.jpeg', '808000.jpg', '461565.jpg', '537667.jpeg', 'Uganda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>Located North East to the wild border with South soudan in Karamoja region, make it the most isolated national park of Uganda, this is transected by the Kidepo and Narus rivers, it is 1442 square kilometers sized park savannah The park is a true wilderness destination for the adventurous and has excellent wildlife-viewing during the Dry season, featuring several species not encountered anywhere else in the country, a home of cheetah,leopard, elephant,hyena, giraffe, zebra, fox etc.</p><p> majors activities are game drives,the sand bed along River Kidepo,Birding, Nature walk, mount Morungole hiking,and Karamajong community tour.</p>', 'Active', '2024-02-27 19:03:45.904870'),
(49, 'Kigali city tour', '75881.jpeg', '933318.jpg', '583009.jpg', '985921.jpg', 'Rwanda', '--- Select Province ---', '--- Select Tour District ---', '<p>This tour offers unforgettable memories of kigali city, the capital of Rwanda and includes different parts of Kigali such as the oldest said neighbourhood of Kigali, local market, shopping mall, car free zones of Kigali, Kigali Genocide Memorial and finally drop off anywhere in Kigali.</span></p><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Inclusions and exclusions</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Inclusions</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">-Vehicle tour transportation with Pick up and drop off in Kigali</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asia